        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 15 at 7:07PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 707 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles southwest of Hartwell, or near Royston, moving southeast at 25
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Hartwell, Royston, Bowman, Canon, Franklin Springs, Bowersville,
Victoria Bryant State Park, Dewy Rose, Nuberg, and Vanna.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
